      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:6:124:2",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " الْفُجْلُ أَصْلُهُ يَقْطَعُ الْبَلْغَمَ وَ لُبُّهُ يَهْضِمُ وَ وَرَقُهُ يَحْدِرُ الْبَوْلَ حَدْراً ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "From him, from Al Sayyari, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Khalid, from Ahmad Bin Al Mubarak, from Abu Usman, from Dorost, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The radish, its root cuts the phlegm, and its core digests, and its leaf flows the urine with a flowing’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "2. It is narrated from the narrator of the previous Hadith from al-Sayyariy from Ahmad ibn Muhammad ibn Khalid from ibn al- Mubarak from abu ‘ Uthman from Durust who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘The essence, roots of radish cuts off phlegm, its core helps digest food and its leaves quicken urine fast.’” "
        ]
      }
    }
